Currently we return false in the response if the operation is not successful:

{code}
<CreateTagsResponse xmlns="http://ec2.amazonaws.com/doc/2010-08-31/"><return>false</return></CreateTagsResponse>
{code}

We don't have a framework for EC2 compliant errors in place and it is too late to add that in 3.3. For now I'll change the service to return a more obvious error.

Even if we don't fix this in 3.3 we should leave the issue open for later, the EC2 error for this is (from AWS CLI output):

{code}
A client error (TagLimitExceeded) occurred: The maximum number of Tags for a resource has been reached.
{
    "Response": {
        "Errors": {
            "Error": {
                "Message": "The maximum number of Tags for a resource has been reached.", 
                "Code": "TagLimitExceeded"
            }
        }, 
        "RequestID": "7108bf65-c4d4-494b-914d-78d621611f8c"
    }
}
A client error (TagLimitExceeded) occurred: The maximum number of Tags for a resource has been reached.
{code}

A fix for this has passed QA and I'll merge to testing later this afternoon unless there are any objections to doing so.

Example of the fix:

{code}
# euca-create-tags --tag a=1 --tag b=1 --tag c=1 --tag d=1 --tag e=1 --tag f=1 --tag g=1 --tag h=1 --tag i=1 --tag j=1 --tag k=1 sg-A0074263
CreateTagsType: The maximum number of Tags for a resource has been reached
{code}
